nodes.bodyText: What is the difference between key and restore key? Are they supposed to be different?

       with:

+    - name: Cache local Maven repository
+      uses: actions/cache@v2

+        key: ${{ runner.os }}-maven-${{ hashFiles('**/pom.xml') }}
+        restore-keys: |

nodes.bodyText: See https://docs.github.com/en/actions/guides/caching-dependencies-to-speed-up-workflows . I just copy-pasted this setup. As I inderstand it the restore keys are optional, and can be used as alternative lookup keys if the main key gives no hit.
